      <h2>Welcome to VCFtools</h2>
      <p><b>VCFtools</b> is a program package designed for working with VCF files, such as those generated by the 1000 Genomes Project.
      The aim of VCFtools is to provide easily accessible methods for working with complex genetic variation data in the form of VCF or BCF files.</p>
      <p>This toolset can be used to do the following operations on VCF files:
      <ul>
          <li>Filter out specific variants</li>
          <li>Compare files</li>
          <li>Summarize variants</li>
          <li>Convert to different file types</li>
          <li>Validate and merge files</li>
			 <li>Create intersections and subsets of variants</li>
      </ul>
      </p>
      <p>VCFtools consists of two parts, a <b>perl module</b> and a <b>binary executable</b>. The perl module is a general Perl API and the binary executable is used for analysis.
      </p>
		<h2>Documentation</h2>
      <p>An extensive list of <b>usage examples</b> to accomplish any of functions above (and many more) can be found <a href="examples.html">here</a>.</p>
		<p><a href="man.html">Manual page</a> <b>documentation</b> for the latest stable release of the binary executable is also available.</p>
      <h2>Download</h2>
      <p>VCFtools can be downloaded by getting the latest stable release from <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/vcftools/files/">Sourceforge</a> or by using subversion to get the latest experimental version.</p>
		<p>Please visit the <a href="downloads.html">downloads</a> page for more information.</p>
